Additional Information



Overview of BoxesOSUpdated: May 13, 2017BoxesOS OverviewBoxesOS is a learning management solution for businesses of all sizes. Its capabilities include 

content management, document management, knowledge management, and others. The software 

was designed and launched by Epazz Inc headquartered in Illinois, United States.
BoxesOS Average Rating  This software product is not yet rated
BoxesOS Typical CustomersCustomers of the software include businesses of all sizes and types. It has been deployed 

in a wide range of major industries some of which include financial services, education, 

legal services, retail and wholesale, healthcare and hospitality, government, automation and 

manufacturing, business process outsourcing, transport, media and entertainment, and others.BoxesOS FeaturesThe content management module of the software aims at providing secure management, 

organization, sharing, and archiving of the enterprise content. Quarterly reports can be presented 

to stakeholders and other important data can be shared over secure links. Remote document 

access and management is offered for efficient workflow and content can be shared via multiple 

channels including websites, emails, RSS feed, and others. 

BoxesOS offers website management for both public and private websites. Email content 

management is offered along with email templates which can be customized. Other important 

services of the software include poll management, content aggregator, customized reporting, file 

management, Active Directory integration, prospect client management, recruiting assessment 

management, and others.
BoxesOS AlternativesPopular Alternatives to BoxesOS: .
BoxesOS Pricing InformationThe price varies according to the business and team size. License for small and medium 

organizations begins from $7,500 for active user under 50. For large organizations, the price 

begins at $45,000 for over 1,000 active users.




