Epazz, Inc. Is Expanding Into Europe With Room Scheduling Software & HMI SoftwareHomeMailFlickrTumblrNewsSportsFinanceCelebrityAnswersGroupsMobileMoreYahooSearchSearchSkip to NavigationSkip to Main ContentSkip to Related Content0Epazz, Inc. Is Expanding Into Europe With Room Scheduling Software & HMI SoftwareMarketwireJanuary 19, 2011ReblogShareTweetShareCHICAGO, IL--(Marketwire - 01/19/11) - Epazz, Inc. (OTC.BB:EPAZ - News) is set to make its products even more readily available to a wider market through its reseller initiatives. Finland has been added to the growing number of markets in which Epazz, Inc. is now open for business, having added others in Asia and South America. Epazz, Inc., with a focus on its fully owned subsidiary DeskFlex, Inc. room scheduling software, has entered into a new partnership to cover more of the market in Europe. The new distribution channel is through Moonsoft, a Finnish company, which specializes in software sales for small and medium size businesses, academic institutions and the public sector including governmental institutions.Moonsoft in Espoo, Finland has positioned itself as the company best able to assist customers to make an informed decision when it comes to selecting the right products and licensing for their needs. Moonsoft, whilst having software sales at the foundation of its business, has positioned itself as seller of the world's leading software products. In addition, Moonsoft also offers professional services, support and tools to help its customers to properly manage the complete software lifecycle. DeskFlex therefore has been added to Moonsoft's reliable and highly regarded lineup.Epazz's Chairman and CEO Shaun Passley has indicated he is confident of the company's products capabilities, which have been endorsed by the clients, and the value they bring to them at this challenging time. He also has confidence in his plans for continuing with expanding market presence. "We will look forward to our relationship with Moonsoft. We believe that Moonsoft will also be a good reseller for AutoHire and Intellisys;" said Shaun Passley.AutoHire is an applicant tracking system that competes favorably with other hiring system providers by providing a wide range of applicant tracking functionality combined with ease of use. The system design is not complicated, making it easy for the user to navigate. Quick access to candidate's records is provided directly from the job postings.Intellisys Integrated Plant Management Control (IPMC), is a hmi software system design for water and wastewater facility management. IPMC is the technology-based strategy for optimizing operations by automatically collecting, managing, organizing and disseminating information for the operations, management, laboratory, maintenance, and engineering functions.About Epazz Inc. Epazz Inc. is an enterprise-wide software company that specializes in providing customized web applications to the corporate world, higher education institutions and the public sector. Epazz Inc has two fully owned subsidiaries in DeskFlex, Inc. and Professional Resources Management, Inc.Epazz BoxesOSv3.0 is the complete business web-based software package for small to mid size businesses, Fortune 500 enterprises, government agencies and higher education institutions. BoxesOS provides many of the web-based applications organizations would have to buy separately.BoxesOS allows for employees to view announcements online. Employees are able to share documents from multiple locations throughout the world. With BoxesOS employees are able to take training courses and their supervisors are able to view the results online. Companies are able to create self-service portals for their customers to pay for their invoice and download instructions. Companies can also create self-service portals for their partners to request new marketing materials or view a demo. BoxesOS connects to companies' databases to easily bring all of their information together.BoxesOS includes an intranet software, portal, extranet, central knowledge repository, document management, workflow engine, website management, web collaboration, email system, and learning management system into one complete web-based solution which connects to organizations' backend systems.BoxesOS allows the organization to start-up by implementing elegant web-enabled information dashboards for each stakeholder group. Functionality with administrative systems can be swiftly completed using BoxesOS connectors to other back-end systems. Business applications that require upgrading can be upgraded on a prioritized basis as desired, and easily linked to BoxesOS and its personal information system."Safe Harbor" statement under the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995:Certain statements contained in this press release are "forward-looking statements" within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Forward-looking statements generally can be identified by the use of forward-looking statements such as "may," "expect," "intend," "estimate," "anticipate," "believe," or "continue" (or the negative thereof) or similar terminology. Such forward-looking statements are subject to risk, uncertainties and other factors that could cause actual results to differ materially from future results or implied by such forward-looking statements. Investors are cautioned that any forward-looking statements are not guarantees of future performance and that actual results may differ materially from those contemplated by such forward-looking statements. Epazz assumes no obligation and does not intend to update these forward-looking statements and takes no obligation to update or correct information prepared by third parties that is not paid for by Epazz. Investors are encouraged to review Epazz's public filings on SEC.gov, including its unaudited and audited financial statements, and its Registration Statement, Form 10-K's and Form 10-Q's, which contain general business information about the Company's operations, results of operations and risks associated with the Company and its operations. Go to www.epazz.com/investors to begin our research on this and others penny stock picks.ReblogShareTweetSharePopular in the CommunityMarine’s Son Weeps in Stepmom’s Arms at Wedding: ‘He Could Feel All of the Emotions in the Room and All of the Love’202 reactions16%67%17%Drawing in the customers in Mogadishu32 reactions5%85%10%Charlie Gard's family ends legal fight: 'We will miss him terribly'2,875 reactions7%66%27%Republican Senator McCain will return Tuesday for healthcare vote761 reactions5%78%17%Two-time Pulitzer Prize winning photographer Muhammed Muheisen33 reactions2%83%15%Human smuggling horror discovered in Texas death trap7 reactions0%58%42%Luis Fonsi On Justin Bieber's Spanish, 'Despacito' Hitting No. 1506 reactions4%79%17%Houston Stripper Maliah Michel Responds to Drake 'Retiring' Her Jersey690 reactions6%77%17%Ariel Winter went pantsless to show the world her new tattoo1,445 reactions5%71%24%Justin Bieber Cancels All Remaining 'Purpose' Tour Dates Due to 'Unforeseen Circumstances'1,647 reactions4%77%19%Bodies found in overheated truck in a Walmart in Texas984 reactions3%76%21%New surveillance video reveals deadly Green Beret shooting2 reactions0%0%100%Historic Pearl River Mart Reopens to Bring 'Cross-Cultural Joy' to NYC207 reactions8%68%24%New York kayak murder case: Woman pleads guilty to negligent homicide in fiance death557 reactions2%74%24%Here's Trump's approval rating in every state267 reactions7%71%22%Yazidi girl held captive by Isis reveals she was raped every day for six months3,893 reactions5%62%33%Republican Senator McCain will return Tuesday for healthcare votePat: IF YOU DO VOTE MR MCCAIN....just remember you had HEALTHCARE for your illness....PAID FOR BY TAXPAYERS....we want the same!!Join the Conversation1 / 5761










